content.description: Start low with two good side pulls, set feet and throw for the ledge. Finish right via fun and easing but attention grabbing slab climbing that wraps up the pillar.  The direct top-out is a little trickier and gets a PG-13 rating(watch the ledge).
content.location: Boulder just up and right 10ft of Beautiful Soup boulder.

content.description: Climb the crux of Beautiful Soup but instead of heading right at the ledge go straight up the finish of Keymaker.  A pure line with no traversing.
content.location: Same start as BS, but head to the top versus traversing to the right.

content.description: Slap up the arete left of Beautiful Soup and topout via the Key Maker.  The arete felt about v7 to the jug break.  Good climbing. Unnamed and unrated, so the grade is just a guess..
content.protection: A number of pads, it is tall.

content.description: Start at the bottom right corner of the Beautiful Soup boulder on an undercling and edge.  Work your way up and left until you get into the start holds of Beautiful Soup.  Do the moves on BS to reach the rail but instead of traversing off right continue straight up to the top of the boulder using a very small, slopey crimper.
content.location: Located 1 boulder uphill from Alpine Club.

content.description: Start on the left hand sidepull crimp and go up right to another small crimp.  Big huck for the rail and then traverse off right to the jug on right side of wall.
content.protection: Landing starts sloping away to the right so bring a few pads.
content.location: Located 1 boulder further uphill from Alpine Club.

content.description: Find your way to Alpine Club. Walk around and above Alpine Club, and you're there.
